    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-01-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-01-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="192"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d192">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 841.857P43/47</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Austro-Hungarian Minister of Foreign Affairs</hi>
                        (<persName corresp="#p_BVRSB1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Burian</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Austro-Hungarian Chargé at Washington</hi>
                        (<persName corresp="#p_ZBE1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Zwiedinek</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vienna</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-01-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 12, 1916</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Handed to the Secretary of State<lb/>by the
                            Chargé, January 12</hi>.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>In answer to Mr. <persName corresp="#p_PFC1">Penfield</persName>’s note of the
                    5th, we informed him that, having received no information with regard to the
                    sinking of the <hi rend="italic">Persia</hi>, we could not assume any
                    responsibility for this action. In a case which would involve our responsibility
                    we should naturally be guided by the principles we agreed to in the <hi
                        rend="italic">Ancona</hi> controversy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BVRSB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Burian</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
